comment: Properties of an ordered pair with a finite first component with at least L elements, proven by finite induction on the size of the first component. This theorem can be applied for graphs (represented as orderd pairs of vertices and edges) with a finite number of vertices, usually with ` L = 0 ` (see ~ opfi1ind ) or ` L = 1 ` . (Contributed by AV, 22-Oct-2020.) (Revised by AV, 28-Mar-2021.)
